6Ô∏è‚É£ Networking Essentials
      VPC = Isolated virtual network
      Security Group = Instance-level firewall (stateful)
      NACL = Subnet-level firewall (stateless)
      Route 53 = DNS
      ELB = Distributes traffic across AZs
      CloudFront = CDN(Content Delivery Network)
      Global Accelerator = Low latency via AWS backbone
      Security Group ‚Üí allow rules only
      NACL ‚Üí allow + deny rules

7Ô∏è‚É£ Monitoring & Logging
      | Service         | Purpose                                  |
      | --------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
      | CloudWatch      | Metrics + alarms                         |
      | CloudTrail      | API logging                              |
      | Config          | Resource configuration history           |
      API activity? ‚Üí CloudTrail
      Config change tracking? ‚Üí Config
      Metrics? ‚Üí CloudWatch

8Ô∏è‚É£ Pricing & Billing 
      Pricing Models
         On-Demand ‚Üí No commitment
         Reserved Instances ‚Üí 1 or 3 year commitment
         Savings Plans ‚Üí Flexible commitment (better modern answer)
         Spot ‚Üí Up to 90% discount, interruptible
         Dedicated Hosts ‚Üí Compliance needs
      Cost Tools
        Cost Explorer ‚Üí Analyze & forecast
        Budgets ‚Üí Alerts
        Pricing Calculator ‚Üí Estimate before deploying
        Consolidated Billing ‚Üí Multiple accounts under one payer
        Trusted Advisor ‚Üí Cost + security + limits recommendations

9Ô∏è‚É£ IAM Essentials   
      IAM User ‚Üí Person/app
      IAM Role ‚Üí Temporary credentials
      IAM Policy ‚Üí JSON permissions
      Root user ‚Üí Lock it down + MFA
      Always follow Least Privilege
      Root Best Practices:
        Enable MFA
        Don‚Äôt use daily
        No access keys

